            Idioms are frequently fossilized metaphors: the thin
red line , which lies at the back of this piece of wordplay,
means the heroic resistance of the few against
many, and originally described a regiment of
redcoated highlanders at the battle of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Balaclava</ENAMEX>.  In
the puns we have been looking at, the <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">writer</ENAMEX> may
revive and extend a metaphor (portraying the <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">teachers</ENAMEX>
as a small embattled <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">force</ENAMEX>, but making them blue
