<NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">83</NUMEX>), You are a humbug! (<ENAMEX TYPE="WORK_OF_ART">Scarecrow to the Wizard</ENAMEX>,
<NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">97</NUMEX>), and I think you are a very bad <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">man</ENAMEX>! (<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Dorothy</ENAMEX> to
the <ENAMEX TYPE="WORK_OF_ART">Wizard</ENAMEX>, <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">100</NUMEX>).  The movie, with its alliterative
abuse, name-calling, taunts, shouting and yelling,
threats, scolding, and nasty sarcasm is much livelier
and much scarier for <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">children</ENAMEX> than the book.  To be
sure, by <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">today</TIMEX>'s standards, the film's most often used
